Examples for using a webserver

Example 1: train schedule as static website (display all trains per day)

* ws-inline-css.py:
  webserver with CSS defined inline
  webserver: localhost on port 8080
  reads train schedule from abfahrtstafel.csv

  call: python3 ws-inline-css.py
  quit: press CTRL+C

* ws-external-css.py:
  webserver with CSS defined in an external file
  webserver: localhost on port 8080
  reads train schedule from abfahrtstafel.csv
  reads CSS from farbschema.css

  call: python3 ws-external-css.py
  quit: press CTRL+C

Example 2: train schedule as dynamic website (remove trains from the
displayed schedule that run in the past)

* ws-inline-css-dynamic.py:
  webserver with CSS defined inline
  webserver: localhost on port 8080
  reads train schedule from abfahrtstafel.csv

  call: python3 ws-inline-css-dynamic.py
  quit: press CTRL+C

* ws-external-css-dynamic.py:
  webserver with CSS defined in an external file
  webserver: localhost on port 8080
  reads train schedule from abfahrtstafel.csv
  reads CSS from farbschema.css

  call: python3 ws-external-css-dynamic.py
  quit: press CTRL+C
